The schoolgirls kidnapped from Government Girls Science Technical College (GGSTC), Dapchi, in Yobe State, have been returned to the town by Boko Haram insurgents, according to report. A resident confirmed the development to our reporter. According to the resident, the insurgents returned the girls in the early hours of Wednesday few minutes after soldiers were withdrawn from the town. “We are happy. There is jubilation in Dapchi now as the girls are back,” the resident said. We are monitoring the story and will update as soon as we have fresh fact. The insurgents invaded the Government Girls Science Technical College (GGSTC), Dapchi, in Yobe State on February 19, and abducted the students. 